headline: CTAS Q1 Deep Dive: Broad-Based Growth and Technology Investments
summary: Uniform and facility services provider Cintas (NASDAQ:CTAS) reported Q3 CY2025 results exceeding the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 8.7% year on year to $2.72 billion. On the other hand, the company’s full-year revenue guidance of $11.12 million at the midpoint came in 99.9% below analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $1.20 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.
